WEBVTT

00:00.810 --> 00:02.150
- ♪

00:02.210 --> 00:05.510
- And, of course, as starting
quarterback, Bella Dawson.

00:05.580 --> 00:08.710
- What, what!

00:08.790 --> 00:12.490
Sorry, it's
just still so exciting.

00:12.560 --> 00:15.260
- Anyway, so that's our
starting lineup for next week.

00:15.330 --> 00:17.930
Newt, you are not starting.

00:18.000 --> 00:21.300
- Who did that?

00:21.370 --> 00:23.140
- All right, one more thing.

00:23.200 --> 00:25.440
Last week's game ball.

00:25.500 --> 00:26.830
Normally we award this

00:26.900 --> 00:28.830
to the most outstanding player
of the game.

00:28.910 --> 00:32.240
But last week, we had
two outstanding players.

00:32.310 --> 00:36.680
I'm awarding the game ball
to both Sawyer and Troy.

00:36.750 --> 00:37.850
- My wide receivers.

00:37.920 --> 00:39.050
What! What!

00:40.820 --> 00:43.690
Promise, last time.

00:43.750 --> 00:46.280
- You guys, uh,
cool with sharing?

00:46.360 --> 00:47.730
- Of course, my good man.

00:47.790 --> 00:49.030
Indubitably.

00:49.090 --> 00:51.150
Care for a spot of tea?

00:52.630 --> 00:53.330
- Oh, wonderful.

00:55.770 --> 00:57.240
- I knew I never should have
turned you guys

00:57.300 --> 00:59.770
onto "Downton Abbey."

00:59.840 --> 01:01.470
Dawson, a word.

01:04.239 --> 01:06.080
- Coach, I know
what this is about.

01:06.140 --> 01:10.270
And, yes, I promise to keep
my "What! What!" under control.

01:11.750 --> 01:13.150
Well, that's not why
I brought you in here,

01:13.220 --> 01:14.490
but I appreciate that.

01:14.550 --> 01:17.920
Yeah, look, Dawson, when you
first joined the team,

01:17.990 --> 01:19.760
I wanted you to learn the game.

01:19.820 --> 01:21.480
Now that you've done that, it's
time you learn

01:21.560 --> 01:24.900
the other part of being
a quarterback--leadership.

01:24.960 --> 01:26.000
- You can count on me, coach.

01:26.060 --> 01:27.590
- Good.

01:27.670 --> 01:29.740
Because leadership is much more
than throwing touchdown passes.

01:29.800 --> 01:31.500
You gotta guys keep these guys
on their workouts

01:31.570 --> 01:34.910
and practice schedules, make
sure they stay out of trouble,

01:34.970 --> 01:36.740
go to class, wash my car.

01:36.810 --> 01:37.780
- Wash your car?

01:37.840 --> 01:40.450
- All a part
of being quarterback.

01:40.510 --> 01:42.780
But the most important thing
a leader does...

01:42.850 --> 01:45.720
is keep the team together
at all costs.

01:45.780 --> 01:48.310
You gotta keep an eye out
for a potential problems.

01:48.390 --> 01:50.460
Little things can turn
into big things

01:50.520 --> 01:52.760
if you don't nip them
in the bud.

01:52.820 --> 01:55.180
- Coach, I was captain
of the cheer squad.

01:55.260 --> 01:57.700
Problem solving was like
the job description.

01:57.760 --> 01:59.770
One time, Taylor and Madison
were arguing over

01:59.830 --> 02:00.430
whether we should yell

02:00.500 --> 02:02.030
"Hustle!" or "Dynamite!"

02:02.100 --> 02:04.240
And I made them turn
their feelings into--

02:04.300 --> 02:06.670
- Oh, that's great.
Girl power.

02:10.710 --> 02:12.180
- Congratulations
on the game ball, guys.

02:12.240 --> 02:14.540
Maybe someday when I'm a starter
I'll get one of those, too.

02:17.110 --> 02:19.070
"Yeah, buddy, it'll happen."

02:19.150 --> 02:21.220
- Oh, yeah, right.
- Oh, yeah.

02:21.290 --> 02:24.020
- Wow, thanks, guys.

02:24.090 --> 02:26.190
- All right, so what do you
think about storing

02:26.260 --> 02:28.530
our game ball in my basement?

02:28.590 --> 02:30.990
I know a nice spot right between
the photo of me fist bumping

02:31.060 --> 02:35.270
Obama and the computer
I used to fake that photo.

02:35.330 --> 02:36.930
- That's an interesting idea.

02:37.000 --> 02:38.800
But I need something to throw at
my rooster in the morning

02:38.870 --> 02:39.970
when I wanna sleep in.

02:40.040 --> 02:41.710
Rooster's don't
have snooze buttons.

02:41.770 --> 02:43.210
- Why don't you guys leave it
somewhere you'll both see it

02:43.270 --> 02:44.600
every day?

02:44.680 --> 02:46.110
- Above the urinals
in the bathroom?

02:46.180 --> 02:47.250
- Oh, good call.

02:47.310 --> 02:48.210
- Oh, man.

02:48.280 --> 02:50.450
- No, dummies.

02:50.510 --> 02:53.340
The locker room.

02:53.420 --> 02:54.450
- That could work, too.

02:54.520 --> 02:55.850
- I mean, I guess.

