- ♪

03:33.990 --> 03:35.230
- It's weird.

03:35.290 --> 03:36.820
You not being a part of
the cheer squad this year.

03:36.890 --> 03:38.990
It feels like the end of an era.

03:39.060 --> 03:40.860
- Well, you may not have me
for the bake sale,

03:40.930 --> 03:45.400
but you do have...
my snicker doodles!

03:45.470 --> 03:48.540
Doodles, doodles, doodles!

03:48.610 --> 03:50.240
This bake sale is
gonna be awesome.

03:50.310 --> 03:53.480
You'll make enough money to pay
for the whole cheer retreat.

03:53.540 --> 03:55.700
I'll help you
get started right now.

03:55.780 --> 03:56.750
- Hey, that's a dollar.

03:56.810 --> 03:58.540
- Mm, this is so awesome.

03:58.620 --> 04:01.150
You need to buy
like four of these.

04:01.220 --> 04:03.190
- Bella owes one dollar.

04:03.250 --> 04:04.210
- Excuse me.

04:04.290 --> 04:06.060
- Or maybe not,
she did make them.

04:06.120 --> 04:07.620
- Excuse me, how much
are these cookies?

04:07.690 --> 04:09.590
- This is a good cause,
and we need the money.

04:09.660 --> 04:10.630
- Make up your mind.

04:10.700 --> 04:12.900
I'm trying to buy
something here.

04:12.960 --> 04:14.490
- I wanna buy something, too.

04:14.570 --> 04:17.200
Your silence.

04:17.269 --> 04:20.209
- How mean.

04:20.269 --> 04:21.640
- Can you believe that guy?

04:21.709 --> 04:23.280
I am not mean.

04:23.340 --> 04:24.110
Am I?

04:24.180 --> 04:24.910
- No.

04:24.980 --> 04:26.240
That guy is rude.

04:26.310 --> 04:27.850
Telling me to make up my mind.

04:27.910 --> 04:31.150
I have no problem
making up my mind.

04:31.220 --> 04:32.420
Or do I?

04:32.480 --> 04:34.240
- No way.

04:34.320 --> 04:37.620
Yo, which one of you cheapstakes
wants to buy a sugar cookie?

04:40.760 --> 04:44.200
- So, coach, if I keep drinking
these and put on

04:44.260 --> 04:47.370
20 pounds of pure muscle,
grow 8 to 10 inches in a month,

04:47.430 --> 04:49.200
you think I could be a starter
for the Bulldogs?

04:50.870 --> 04:52.800
You ever considered ping pong?

04:52.870 --> 04:54.540
You certainly have
the bone structure.

04:54.610 --> 04:56.010
Oh, I mean I--

04:56.070 --> 04:58.170
- Oh, look,
the bake sale's starting.

04:58.240 --> 05:02.810
Snickerdoodles here I come.

05:02.880 --> 05:03.850
- Good to see everybody's

05:03.910 --> 05:05.470
following
their workout schedule.

05:05.550 --> 05:06.990
If anyone has any questions,

05:07.050 --> 05:08.990
I took the weight-room
orientation class.

05:09.050 --> 05:10.650
- Hey, Bella,
you wanna spot me?

05:10.720 --> 05:13.460
- QB at your service.

05:13.520 --> 05:14.950
- Uh, all right,
I gotta warn you.

05:15.030 --> 05:17.000
This is the get psyched
portion of my workout so--

05:24.140 --> 05:26.540
Ow!

05:26.600 --> 05:30.300
Cardboard bruise.

05:30.370 --> 05:32.200
- Troy, I might be awhile.

05:32.280 --> 05:34.380
This machine will probably
wear out before my arms do.

05:34.450 --> 05:35.880
- Ah, no worries.

05:35.950 --> 05:38.880
It'll give the Troy more time to
practice my post-game interview.

05:38.950 --> 05:41.620
I wanna come off
as humble yet extraordinary.

05:45.390 --> 05:47.530
- Yeah, 'cause nothing says
humble like putting

05:47.590 --> 05:49.560
a "the" in front of your name.

05:49.630 --> 05:52.400
- This coming from a guy who
wears a five-pound belt buckle.

05:52.460 --> 05:54.420
We get it, you're from Texas.

05:54.500 --> 05:57.300
We all are.

05:57.370 --> 05:59.140
- Do they always
argue like this?

05:59.200 --> 06:00.400
- Well, they've always been
competitive,

06:00.470 --> 06:02.740
but things have gotten personal.

06:02.810 --> 06:04.740
- I--I guess it makes sense.

06:04.810 --> 06:06.950
Troy and Sawyer are both
playing the same position.

06:07.010 --> 06:09.980
And they both wanna be
the number-one receiver.

06:10.050 --> 06:11.680
I wonder if this is
gonna be an issue.

06:12.680 --> 06:14.180
You're a real funny guy, Troy.

06:14.250 --> 06:15.250
Funny smellin'.

06:15.320 --> 06:17.120
- I think you're
smelling my butt,

06:17.190 --> 06:19.390
because you're so slow,
you're always behind me.

06:19.460 --> 06:20.390
- So your butt smells?

06:20.460 --> 06:21.560
- Yeah.

06:21.630 --> 06:22.460
Wait.

06:22.530 --> 06:24.130
You know what I mean.

06:24.200 --> 06:26.630
- Whoa, guys, can we please
just agree

06:26.700 --> 06:29.940
that everybody's butt smells?

06:30.000 --> 06:32.540
Now let's get back
to getting buff!

06:34.310 --> 06:35.410
- Okay.

06:35.470 --> 06:36.630
I'm gonna do some sit-ups.

06:36.710 --> 06:38.680
I think I'll do about 500.

06:38.740 --> 06:40.780
- Wait, yeah,
well, I'm gonna 501.

06:43.410 --> 06:45.870
- Oh, man, this is
gonna be an issue.

06:45.950 --> 06:47.390
I've gotta do
something about this.

06:47.450 --> 06:49.220
- Bella, help.

06:49.290 --> 06:52.760
- Oops, sorry, Newt.

06:52.820 --> 06:54.450
- You saved my life.

06:54.530 --> 06:56.030
But hurt my pride.

06:59.930 --> 07:01.770
- On the other hand, if you
want sweet and salty,

07:01.830 --> 07:03.540
I'd go with
the salted caramel brownies.

07:03.600 --> 07:05.570
- Great, I'll have those.

07:05.640 --> 07:08.940
- Then again...if you just want
something salty, oh,

07:09.010 --> 07:11.010
I'd go to the vending machine
and get some barbeque chips.

07:11.080 --> 07:13.480
- Ooh, barbeque
does sound good.

07:13.540 --> 07:14.540
Thanks.

07:14.610 --> 07:17.280
- No problem.

07:17.350 --> 07:18.080
What?

07:18.150 --> 07:20.550
She just wanted some chips.

07:20.620 --> 07:22.520
- Pepper, you just
lost us a sale.

07:22.590 --> 07:24.820
You keep giving customers 30
choices, including the option

07:24.890 --> 07:26.530
to not buy anything at all.

07:26.590 --> 07:28.260
You're completely indecisive.

07:28.330 --> 07:29.460
- Well, you're mean.

07:29.530 --> 07:31.030
You made that one girl cry.

07:31.100 --> 07:32.760
- She was trying
to pay with pennies.

07:32.830 --> 07:35.430
- She was six.

07:35.500 --> 07:37.370
- Oh my gosh, I am mean.

07:37.430 --> 07:38.560
- You are.

07:38.640 --> 07:41.740
And I kinda think I might
be indecisive, maybe.

07:43.870 --> 07:45.900
- No wonder we haven't
been selling anything.

07:45.980 --> 07:48.410
- We can't handle this
at all without Bella.

07:48.480 --> 07:50.620
I need a brownie.

07:50.680 --> 07:53.020
Or a lemon square.

07:53.080 --> 07:56.140
These flavors do not blend well.

07:56.220 --> 07:59.120
- No, we can handle
this on our own.

07:59.190 --> 08:00.830
We just have to
change our approach.

08:00.890 --> 08:03.030
From now on, I'll be nice
and you'll be--

08:03.090 --> 08:05.490
- Mm, there's so many
different things I could be.

08:05.560 --> 08:06.920
A doctor, a lawyer.

08:07.000 --> 08:08.070
The president.

08:08.130 --> 08:08.600
- Pepper.

08:08.670 --> 08:09.500
- Decisive.

08:09.570 --> 08:10.870
I will be decisive.

08:14.410 --> 08:14.970
- Hey, guys.

08:15.040 --> 08:16.470
Thanks for coming.

08:16.540 --> 08:19.710
So I was thinking maybe we could
do some team-bonding exercises

08:19.780 --> 08:21.810
I used when I was cheer captain.

08:21.880 --> 08:23.580
- Okay, fine.
- That's weird.

08:23.650 --> 08:25.920
- Okay, Newt's gonna help
demonstrate the first exercise.

08:25.980 --> 08:27.440
This is a trust fall.

08:27.520 --> 08:31.320
Before you fall, tell me one
fear that you want to let go of.

08:31.390 --> 08:34.590
I'm afraid of trust falls.

08:34.659 --> 08:37.299
I feel so alive.

08:37.360 --> 08:38.000
- All right.

08:38.059 --> 08:39.059
Sawyer, you go first.

08:39.130 --> 08:40.470
Troy, you catch him.

08:40.530 --> 08:43.570
Sawyer, what's your fear?

08:43.630 --> 08:45.330
- I'm afraid of the goat man.

08:45.400 --> 08:47.910
- Yeah, I don't know
what the goat man is,

08:47.970 --> 08:51.280
but we're not doing that.

08:51.340 --> 08:53.910
- I don't know, goat man
sounds pretty scary to me.

08:53.980 --> 08:55.680
- Newt, focus.

08:55.750 --> 08:58.280
- All right, Sawyer, why don't
you talk about another fear?

08:58.350 --> 09:00.750
Maybe something team related,
like--just a thought--

09:00.820 --> 09:02.590
what y'all been
arguing about all week.

09:02.650 --> 09:03.450
- Arguing?

09:03.520 --> 09:04.520
We haven't been arguing?

09:04.590 --> 09:06.160
We're just kidding around.

09:06.220 --> 09:07.420
- Yeah, Bella, we're bros.

09:07.490 --> 09:08.990
It's what we do.

09:09.060 --> 09:10.800
- Come on, guys, I think it's
pretty obvious

09:10.860 --> 09:12.600
what's going on here.

09:12.660 --> 09:14.620
You're sharing the same position
now, and you both wanna be

09:14.700 --> 09:16.700
the number-one receiver.

09:16.770 --> 09:18.470
- Why would I be
afraid of that?

09:18.540 --> 09:20.170
I've mean a great wide receiver
for years,

09:20.240 --> 09:21.640
and I've got the game ball
to prove it.

09:21.710 --> 09:23.340
- Uh, half the game ball.

09:23.410 --> 09:24.940
And don't forget, I wasn't
even a wide receiver

09:25.010 --> 09:26.580
at the start of the season.

09:26.640 --> 09:28.070
And I already caught up to you.

09:28.150 --> 09:30.080
Next week, I'm gonna have
that game ball all to myself.

09:30.150 --> 09:32.150
Deal with it, Huggins.

09:32.220 --> 09:34.250
- Well, what if I don't
wanna deal with it?

09:34.320 --> 09:36.960
- Hey, hey, can't we just
go back to the trust falls?

09:37.020 --> 09:38.690
I'm afraid this isn't working.

09:43.330 --> 09:45.300
- I'm okay.

09:45.360 --> 09:48.530
- Okay, uh...let's try another
technique I used

09:48.600 --> 09:50.300
when I was cheer captain.

09:50.370 --> 09:54.240
Express yourself in the form
of an "I feel" statement.

09:54.300 --> 09:55.460
- Fine.

09:55.540 --> 09:58.680
I feel Troy's a jerk, and I feel
sick of him always

09:58.740 --> 09:59.880
having to be the best.

09:59.940 --> 10:01.870
- And I feel like somebody's
a big baby,

10:01.950 --> 10:03.620
just like
at peewee sleepaway camp.

10:03.680 --> 10:06.580
Sawyer pee-weed all up
in his sleeping bag.

10:06.650 --> 10:08.150
- At least I didn't cry myself
to sleep every night

10:08.220 --> 10:10.060
like Teary Troy the Blumper Boy.

10:10.120 --> 10:11.460
- Use "I feel" statements.

10:11.520 --> 10:14.390
- Fine, I feel like
my fist belongs in your face.

10:14.460 --> 10:15.360
- Oh, yeah?

10:15.430 --> 10:16.430
Well, I feel like
my foot belongs

10:16.490 --> 10:18.250
somewhere it's not polite
to talk about.

10:18.330 --> 10:21.230
- I feel like I'm gonna puke.

10:21.300 --> 10:22.000
- Argh!

10:22.070 --> 10:23.370
- Guys, stop!

10:23.430 --> 10:25.430
You're teammates,
stop it, break it up!

10:26.170 --> 10:26.870
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!

10:26.940 --> 10:29.410
Break it up!

10:29.470 --> 10:32.430
Troy, Sawyer, get
in my office now!

10:32.510 --> 10:33.140
- But, coach--

10:33.210 --> 10:34.510
- I don't wanna hear it!

10:38.380 --> 10:39.880
- What are you
gonna do to them?

10:39.950 --> 10:41.590
- I'm suspending
them from the team.

10:45.960 --> 10:48.030
- Does anyone have an extra
toothbrush in their locker?

10:53.760 --> 10:55.790
- ♪

10:55.870 --> 10:57.100
- Coach, let me explain.

10:57.170 --> 10:58.800
It was a misunderstanding.

10:58.870 --> 11:00.000
- I know what I saw.

